00:35:37,034 --> 00:35:38,603
<i>Ramyeon</i> soup base?

950
00:35:38,669 --> 00:35:39,670
-Soup base?
-What's that?

951
00:35:39,737 --> 00:35:41,005
-<i>Ramyeon</i> soup?
-What?

952
00:35:41,072 --> 00:35:43,374
Why are you mixing it with cold water?

953
00:35:43,441 --> 00:35:45,443
I just wanted to do it now
before I forget.

954
00:35:45,843 --> 00:35:47,145
IN CASE HE FORGETS

955
00:35:47,211 --> 00:35:49,247
-What about the heat?
-You can turn it on, right?

956
00:35:49,313 --> 00:35:50,381
I have to do it later.

957
00:35:50,448 --> 00:35:52,316
He has changed after winning.

958
00:35:52,383 --> 00:35:53,651
He looks very relaxed.

959
00:35:54,318 --> 00:35:55,553
LET'S SEE…

960
00:35:55,953 --> 00:35:56,954
MIXES THE SOY SAUCE

961
00:35:57,021 --> 00:36:00,224
Kang-rok may finish in three minutes
if he doesn't talk.

962
00:36:00,291 --> 00:36:02,360
You're right. I don't see much.

963
00:36:02,426 --> 00:36:04,428
STANDING AROUND

964
00:36:04,896 --> 00:36:08,065
THE SELLOUT KING
BEGINS TO CHOP GREEN ONION

965
00:36:10,368 --> 00:36:11,435
They're both using green onion.

966
00:36:11,736 --> 00:36:13,471
CHOPPING

967
00:36:13,538 --> 00:36:16,908
HE USED TO MAKE EVERYONE FRUSTRATED
WITH HIS SLOW-PACED CHOPPING

968
00:36:17,241 --> 00:36:19,510
BUT HE'S RACING TODAY!

969
00:36:19,577 --> 00:36:22,513
THIS IS HOW THE WINNER OF CCW2 CHOPS

970
00:36:22,580 --> 00:36:24,582
That's so thin.

971
00:36:25,483 --> 00:36:27,818
THE CHOPPING BATTLE

972
00:36:27,885 --> 00:36:29,554
The chopping battle.

973
00:36:29,854 --> 00:36:31,222
MEERKAT MODE

974
00:36:31,289 --> 00:36:34,025
They studied
at the same culinary institute.

975
00:36:34,091 --> 00:36:35,226
They went to the same school.

976
00:36:35,293 --> 00:36:36,761
Ho-young even gave Kang-rok
a part-time job.

977
00:36:36,827 --> 00:36:41,132
Add chili oil and stir-fry
garlic and green onion.

978
00:36:41,199 --> 00:36:44,302
-I see. Chili oil.
-Why won't it come out?

979
00:36:44,368 --> 00:36:46,070
All you have to do is squeeze.

980
00:36:47,605 --> 00:36:49,340
That's a good tip.

981
00:36:49,407 --> 00:36:51,642
-You don't have to share that too.
-Thank you.

982
00:36:51,709 --> 00:36:53,177
That was a great tip.

983
00:36:53,244 --> 00:36:54,712
-A great tip.
-He's got so many.

984
00:36:54,779 --> 00:36:56,647
It's because many kids watch this too.

985
00:36:56,714 --> 00:36:58,015
That's right.

986
00:36:58,082 --> 00:37:00,318
-But he…
-Here's the thickness.

987
00:37:01,786 --> 00:37:04,121
IT SHOULD BE ABOUT THIS THICK, CHILDREN

988
00:37:04,855 --> 00:37:07,325
-It's silky.
-Silky batter.

989
00:37:07,391 --> 00:37:10,161
It's a bit thinner
than the usual sweet and sour beef batter.

990
00:37:10,228 --> 00:37:11,762
-Yes.
-It's pretty thin.

991
00:37:11,829 --> 00:37:14,232
-I hope he adds some more starch.
-Is it okay?

992
00:37:14,298 --> 00:37:16,534
The beef is in great quality,

993
00:37:16,601 --> 00:37:19,704
-so the batter shouldn't be too thick.
-Don't make it thick.

994
00:37:19,770 --> 00:37:20,972
A-HA

995
00:37:21,038 --> 00:37:22,974
Make it thin so you can taste the beef.

996
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:25,810
It's more like Japanese-style fritters.

997
00:37:26,110 --> 00:37:27,478
HOWEVER…

998
00:37:27,545 --> 00:37:28,546
Gosh.

999
00:37:28,613 --> 00:37:30,181
Huh? Something isn't right.

1000
00:37:30,248 --> 00:37:31,482
You know what?

1001
00:37:32,049 --> 00:37:33,718
The batter seems a bit too thin.

1002
00:37:33,784 --> 00:37:35,353
POURING A LOT OF STARCH

1003
00:37:35,419 --> 00:37:36,821
-I knew something was wrong!
-Right?

1004
00:37:36,887 --> 00:37:38,589
We all thought it looked too thin.

1005
00:37:38,956 --> 00:37:40,825
WE KNEW IT WAS A BIT TOO THIN

1006
00:37:40,891 --> 00:37:43,394
-I thought he had a way to fix it.
-This is the perfect thickness.

1007
00:37:43,961 --> 00:37:46,063
You're adding them to the same pot
as the failed ones?

1008
00:37:46,764 --> 00:37:47,832
I knew this would happen,

1009
00:37:47,898 --> 00:37:49,934
so I prepared two pots of hot oil.

1010
00:37:50,001 --> 00:37:51,235
…two pots of hot oil.

1011
00:37:52,703 --> 00:37:55,206
ASTONISHED

1012
00:37:55,273 --> 00:37:57,241
-Ho-young.
-After you compete in <i>CCW</i>,

1013
00:37:57,308 --> 00:37:58,709
you always think of a plan B.

1014
00:37:59,076 --> 00:38:00,878
IMPROVISATION LEARNED ON HOME SHOPPING

1015
00:38:00,945 --> 00:38:02,613
This truly is a variety show.

1016
00:38:02,680 --> 00:38:05,983
He looks gentle,
but he's as vicious as a viper.

1017
00:38:06,050 --> 00:38:08,119
He knew this would happen
and prepared two pots.

1018
00:38:08,185 --> 00:38:09,854
I like this recipe.

1019
00:38:10,354 --> 00:38:13,057
WHAT'S MR. RELAXED UP TO?

1020
00:38:14,258 --> 00:38:16,427
He puts green onion in water

1021
00:38:16,494 --> 00:38:18,529
to get rid of its spiciness.

1022
00:38:18,596 --> 00:38:20,965
Yes, take the green onion

1023
00:38:21,032 --> 00:38:22,500
and put it in cold water.

1024
00:38:22,566 --> 00:38:23,567
-Yes?
-And remove?

1025
00:38:23,634 --> 00:38:25,636
And remove the spiciness.

1026
00:38:25,970 --> 00:38:26,971
WE THOUGHT SO

1027
00:38:27,038 --> 00:38:28,506
"And remove the spiciness."

1028
00:38:28,572 --> 00:38:29,874
-He sounds like AI.
-All right.

1029
00:38:30,541 --> 00:38:33,177
I feel so nervous
about him not turning on the heat.

1030
00:38:33,744 --> 00:38:34,945
THE HEAT?

1031
00:38:35,346 --> 00:38:36,981
FIDGETING

1032
00:38:38,149 --> 00:38:40,017
LIGHTS THE STOVE SLOWLY

1033
00:38:40,251 --> 00:38:41,252
FRUSTRATED

1034
00:38:41,319 --> 00:38:43,621
-It's been over five minutes. Hurry.
-Chef Kang-rok.

1035
00:38:43,688 --> 00:38:45,389
You'll have to hurry now.

1036
00:38:45,456 --> 00:38:46,457
WHAT'S NEXT?

1037
00:38:46,524 --> 00:38:47,925
I know the loss is mine, but…

1038
00:38:48,726 --> 00:38:49,794
Wait, what now?

1039
00:38:52,363 --> 00:38:56,567
3. CUBE TOFU

1040
00:38:56,634 --> 00:38:58,169
CHOP

1041
00:38:58,235 --> 00:39:00,338
Chef Kang-rok, is that tofu?

1042
00:39:00,404 --> 00:39:02,373
-In there?
-Tofu and <i>jjamppong ramyeon</i>?

1043
00:39:02,440 --> 00:39:04,675
Yes, this is

1044
00:39:05,209 --> 00:39:07,178
-a bonus.
-A bonus?

1045
00:39:07,244 --> 00:39:08,679
You said you liked <i>tteokbokki</i>,

1046
00:39:08,746 --> 00:39:10,948
so I prepared something to eat on the side

1047
00:39:11,015 --> 00:39:12,616
with <i>tteokbokki</i>.

1048
00:39:12,683 --> 00:39:14,518
MOVED

1049
00:39:14,585 --> 00:39:15,586
"With <i>tteokbokki</i>."

1050
00:39:15,653 --> 00:39:18,022
Something that would
also go well with <i>tteokbokki</i>.

1051
00:39:18,089 --> 00:39:19,957
But I'm not making <i>tteokbokki</i>.

1052
00:39:20,024 --> 00:39:21,192
I'll imagine it.

1053
00:39:21,258 --> 00:39:23,861
That's just water,
<i>ramyeon</i> soup base, and tofu?

1054
00:39:23,928 --> 00:39:25,529
-Yes.
-Really?

1055
00:39:25,596 --> 00:39:27,565
-He'll probably add more stuff.
-He will, right?

1056
00:39:27,932 --> 00:39:29,700
AND NOW, STANDING STILL BY THE MICROWAVE

1057
00:39:29,767 --> 00:39:31,035
He seems quite relaxed.

1058
00:39:31,102 --> 00:39:32,603
Someone help him with the microwave.

1059
00:39:32,670 --> 00:39:34,338
Just put it in and push the button.

1060
00:39:34,405 --> 00:39:37,341
You can just start it,
then adjust the time later,

1061
00:39:37,408 --> 00:39:39,143
but he always
puts in the right time first.

1062
00:39:39,910 --> 00:39:41,045
ROTATING

1063
00:39:41,779 --> 00:39:43,314
-Is it on?
-It has to be exact.

1064
00:39:43,381 --> 00:39:44,982
You have eight minutes
and ten seconds left.

1065
00:39:45,049 --> 00:39:47,551
I'll start making the sauce now.
First, ketchup.

1066
00:39:47,618 --> 00:39:49,754
-Ketchup.
-One ketchup.

1067
00:39:49,820 --> 00:39:51,322
-One ketchup.
-One sugar.

1068
00:39:51,389 --> 00:39:52,923
-One sugar.
-I love the recipe.

1069
00:39:52,990 --> 00:39:54,625
-One vinegar.
-One vinegar.

1070
00:39:54,692 --> 00:39:57,161
He also had

1071
00:39:57,228 --> 00:39:59,830
-delicious cooking wine, so that.
-Cooking wine.

1072
00:39:59,897 --> 00:40:01,132
-One cooking wine.
-How much?

1073
00:40:01,198 --> 00:40:02,433
-One cooking wine.
-One again.

1074
00:40:02,500 --> 00:40:05,603
-To add some spiciness, Lao Gan Ma.
-Lao Gan Ma.

1075
00:40:05,669 --> 00:40:07,405
-You're adding Lao Gan Ma?
-I'll try this

1076
00:40:07,471 --> 00:40:08,973
and fix it if it tastes odd.

1077
00:40:09,974 --> 00:40:10,975
It's easy.

1078
00:40:11,041 --> 00:40:12,877
The ratio was one to one to one to one.

1079
00:40:12,943 --> 00:40:14,412
This…

1080
00:40:14,478 --> 00:40:16,147
MR. RELAXED IS MOTIVATED
BY THE NEXT CHANNEL

1081
00:40:16,213 --> 00:40:17,214
What do you need?

1082
00:40:17,281 --> 00:40:18,916
It's right here.

1083
00:40:18,983 --> 00:40:20,084
Perilla oil.

1084
00:40:20,151 --> 00:40:21,152
Is that perilla oil?

1085
00:40:21,218 --> 00:40:24,088
Depending on the quality
of the salmon roe,

1086
00:40:24,155 --> 00:40:25,489
it may taste fishy.

1087
00:40:25,556 --> 00:40:27,725
-I see. It must be fishy.
-That's why

1088
00:40:27,792 --> 00:40:29,727
-you need perilla oil.
-Perilla oil.

1089
00:40:29,794 --> 00:40:31,695
And you say this as you add it.

1090
00:40:31,762 --> 00:40:33,230
What do you say?

1091
00:40:33,297 --> 00:40:34,865
-Do you say something?
-What do you say?

1092
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:37,234
"It's me."

1093
00:40:37,301 --> 00:40:38,302
RUNS AWAY

1094
00:40:38,369 --> 00:40:39,403
-What do you say?
-"It's me."

1095
00:40:39,470 --> 00:40:40,538
It's me.

1096
00:40:40,604 --> 00:40:42,173
IT'S ME, PERILLA OIL

1097
00:40:42,807 --> 00:40:46,143
SUCCESSFULLY FILMED HIM
SAYING HIS FAMOUS LINE

1098
00:40:46,210 --> 00:40:48,479
Does perilla oil help
remove the fishy taste?

1099
00:40:48,546 --> 00:40:51,415
It's frozen salmon roe,
so it might be fishy.

1100
00:40:51,982 --> 00:40:54,251
Yes, but I had a taste.

1101
00:40:54,819 --> 00:40:57,321
The membranes were quite thin,
and it was great quality.

1102
00:40:57,388 --> 00:40:59,623
-Great quality.
-It is of great quality.

1103
00:40:59,690 --> 00:41:01,292
Six minutes left.

1104
00:41:01,358 --> 00:41:02,660
But Kang-rok still looks relaxed.

1105
00:41:03,227 --> 00:41:05,896
He removed the spiciness
from the green onion.

1106
00:41:05,963 --> 00:41:06,964
WHAT'S ON THE SHOPPING CHANNEL?

1107
00:41:10,034 --> 00:41:11,168
It looks good.

1108
00:41:11,235 --> 00:41:12,303
-It does.
-It looks good.

1109
00:41:12,369 --> 00:41:13,838
Six minutes and thirty seconds.

1110
00:41:13,904 --> 00:41:15,506
Six minutes and thirty seconds.

1111
00:41:16,173 --> 00:41:17,508
He remembered something.

1112
00:41:17,575 --> 00:41:19,577
-Can you deep-fry that quickly?
-What's that?

1113
00:41:19,643 --> 00:41:21,111
He said he'd deep-fry corn too.

1114
00:41:21,178 --> 00:41:22,179
Are you frying corn too?

1115
00:41:23,481 --> 00:41:25,349
Ho-young has skipped lots of steps.

1116
00:41:25,416 --> 00:41:27,585
-He's suddenly in a hurry.
-He's in a hurry.

1117
00:41:27,651 --> 00:41:29,053
THE SELLOUT KING GOES SILENT

1118
00:41:29,119 --> 00:41:31,055
No matter how urgent it is,
you must comment.

1119
00:41:31,121 --> 00:41:32,957
I'll be quiet for a moment.

1120
00:41:33,524 --> 00:41:34,758
ANNOUNCES A BREAK

1121
00:41:34,825 --> 00:41:36,594
Something didn't go right.

1122
00:41:36,660 --> 00:41:40,698
-Things must've gone out of step.
-Starting with the batter.

1123
00:41:40,764 --> 00:41:42,867
-It's hard to stay focused on two things.
-It is.

1124
00:41:42,933 --> 00:41:45,169
-What's up?
-The thickness isn't right.

1125
00:41:45,236 --> 00:41:47,705
-It's an emergency.
-It's sticking to his hands.

1126
00:41:47,771 --> 00:41:49,974
-The thickness.
-It's too sticky.

1127
00:41:50,040 --> 00:41:52,510
-Isn't that too thin?
-This is too funny.

1128
00:41:52,843 --> 00:41:53,844
5. DEEP-FRY CORN BATTER

1129
00:41:53,911 --> 00:41:56,480
-The corn.
-The corn?

1130
00:41:56,547 --> 00:41:58,849
-It's like corn <i>basi</i>.
-Like corn <i>basi</i>.

1131
00:41:58,916 --> 00:42:00,251
But he added shrimps.

1132
00:42:00,885 --> 00:42:04,088
WHILE THE SELLOUT KING REMAINS SILENT…

1133
00:42:04,154 --> 00:42:06,023
And now, this is a very important step.

1134
00:42:06,090 --> 00:42:07,658
GETS EVERYONE'S ATTENTION

1135
00:42:07,725 --> 00:42:09,860
Why are you suddenly talking so fast?

1136
00:42:09,927 --> 00:42:11,996
-Rice needs to be extra hot.
-Hot rice.

1137
00:42:12,062 --> 00:42:13,964
-Keep the egg whites cold.
-Cold egg whites.

1138
00:42:14,031 --> 00:42:16,100
-And separate the yolk.
-Separate the yolk.

1139
00:42:16,166 --> 00:42:17,167
Add egg whites.

1140
00:42:17,234 --> 00:42:18,602
-Add egg whites.
-Into the hot rice.

1141
00:42:18,669 --> 00:42:19,670
-And?
-And mix well.

1142
00:42:19,737 --> 00:42:20,738
Mix well.

1143
00:42:20,804 --> 00:42:23,140
If the rice is freshly cooked,
use chopsticks.

1144
00:42:23,207 --> 00:42:24,808
But you can use a spoon on instant rice.

1145
00:42:24,875 --> 00:42:26,210
-I see.
-Instant rice, a spoon.

1146
00:42:26,277 --> 00:42:27,411
That's easy to remember.

1147
00:42:27,478 --> 00:42:29,547
-Fresh rice, chopsticks.
-Fresh rice, chopsticks.

1148
00:42:29,613 --> 00:42:31,515
-Instant rice, a spoon.
-Yes.

1149
00:42:31,582 --> 00:42:33,250
That's so catchy.

1150
00:42:33,317 --> 00:42:36,420
-Sung-ju, can you report from the kitchen?
-Yes!

1151
00:42:36,487 --> 00:42:38,422
-Five minutes!
-Come with me, Hyun-suk.

1152
00:42:38,489 --> 00:42:40,324
-Grandpa, go. Tank Boy!
-Grandpa.

1153
00:42:40,658 --> 00:42:42,426
CHECKING THE SAUCE BEFORE THEY COME

1154
00:42:42,493 --> 00:42:43,827
You're adding something more.

1155
00:42:43,894 --> 00:42:45,195
Yes, but the ratio is the same.

1156
00:42:45,262 --> 00:42:47,298
He's making the sauce again.

1157
00:42:47,364 --> 00:42:49,667
I guess it wasn't seasoned well.

1158
00:42:49,733 --> 00:42:50,968
Vinegar.

1159
00:42:51,502 --> 00:42:52,836
IT WAS ACTUALLY COOKING WINE

1160
00:42:52,903 --> 00:42:54,238
-Dang it. Hey, man.
-He spilled vinegar.

1161
00:42:54,305 --> 00:42:56,240
THE SELLOUT KING SUDDENLY TALKS CASUALLY

1162
00:42:56,307 --> 00:42:57,741
Who are you talking to?

1163
00:42:57,808 --> 00:43:00,110
The ratio is meaningless at this point.

1164
00:43:00,177 --> 00:43:02,012
No, it's still one to one to one to one.

1165
00:43:02,079 --> 00:43:03,647
-One to one to one to one.
-One to one.

1166
00:43:04,248 --> 00:43:05,349
GLANCES

1167
00:43:05,616 --> 00:43:07,251
STILL RELAXED EVEN AFTER CHECKING THE TIME

1168
00:43:07,318 --> 00:43:10,254
-He's adding the salmon roe soy sauce.
-The soy sauce.

1169
00:43:10,321 --> 00:43:12,623
-Kang-rok's doing something.
-The salmon roe soy sauce.

1170
00:43:12,690 --> 00:43:14,024
May I try this?

1171
00:43:14,091 --> 00:43:15,926
-You may.
-The salmon roe soy sauce.

1172
00:43:16,660 --> 00:43:19,196
Mashed salmon roe and soy sauce

1173
00:43:19,263 --> 00:43:20,731
in a certain ratio.

1174
00:43:20,798 --> 00:43:23,133
WHAT'S IT LIKE?

1175
00:43:23,200 --> 00:43:25,603
Is it good enough to let him win here?

1176
00:43:25,669 --> 00:43:27,972
CAN HE ALSO WIN HERE AT CHEF & MY FRIDGE?

1177
00:43:31,308 --> 00:43:32,476
WHAT'S WITH THAT REACTION?

1178
00:43:32,543 --> 00:43:33,911
-What's wrong?
-Tell us!

1179
00:43:33,978 --> 00:43:35,579
You have my support, Rok!

1180
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:38,015
-What is it?
-What's wrong?

1181
00:43:38,082 --> 00:43:40,150
-Why? It's just the sauce.
-Is it too fishy?

1182
00:43:40,217 --> 00:43:42,419
It's both salty and fishy
at the same time.

1183
00:43:42,486 --> 00:43:45,823
It tastes like the liquid version
of braised anchovies.

1184
00:43:45,889 --> 00:43:48,392
-The liquid version of braised anchovies.
-Braised anchovies.

1185
00:43:48,459 --> 00:43:49,994
-The soup?
-Braised anchovies?

1186
00:43:50,060 --> 00:43:53,230
-It tastes like anchovies.
-Anchovy soy sauce?

1187
00:43:53,297 --> 00:43:54,698
The soup is ready.

1188
00:43:54,765 --> 00:43:56,100
He's throwing them in here.

1189
00:43:56,433 --> 00:43:58,035
ADDING 2 RAW EGGS

1190
00:43:58,102 --> 00:44:00,704
Is that the <i>ramyeon</i> soup base with tofu?

1191
